ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I wouldn't recommend this course to an F&ES student unless this was an area of particular interest for them, just because it was not particularly relevant.
You basically read a few papers a week; it's fun.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I have a deeper knowledge of parameters affecting historical trends in evolution. I also have a better sense of the siloed nature of academia.
This course helped me to understand the complexities of detecting biome shifts on phylogenies, which is relevant to my interests in phylogenetics. I read a lot of papers that are relevant to me.
